PERMITTED USES

Visitors to MathsEdu.org may:

  - View and use material for personal study and self-directed learning
  - Reference content in academic work and research with proper
    attribution
  - Link directly to pages on MathsEdu.org from external websites
  - Display material during non-commercial classroom teaching,
    provided the material is not redistributed, attribution to
    MathsEdu.org is maintained, and access is limited to
    instructional use

RESTRICTIONS

The following activities are strictly prohibited without prior
written permission:

  - Copying or republishing content on other websites or platforms
  - Distributing site content in textbooks or commercial educational
    courses
  - Reproducing diagrams or visualisations in publications or
    presentations
  - Incorporating content into paid educational products or services
  - Mirroring or archiving substantial portions of the website
  - Scraping or extracting content for data collection purposes
  - Using content for training artificial intelligence or machine
    learning models, large language models, or other AI systems

